<br />
Also, if indeed he had told me of the meeting he had to attend, how come he kept me waiting and not bring up the meeting bit when I asked him for the plat. He would have at least said.. <br />
&quot;But.. but.. you said its ok and that I can pay you later or that I have a meeting to attend&quot; or atleast something to that effect. If he indeed told me of the meeting, why do you think I stood there waiting on him for at least 15 minutes to pay me. He never had told me he'll pay me afterwards on <b>another day</b> as he told you. Sure they all have a meeting to attend. Now, dont they ? Once again, clear lies and I'm not a bit surprised coming from him. Does he have any screenshots to prove what he said to you at all. My screenshot doesn't show any. If it does on his, please ask him to submit it on here.<br />
<br />
Take another look at his character flaw. His first obligation was to pay me. Instead, he kept me waiting for at least 10-15 mins when he could have easlily given me the money that he owes me. When I asked him for the plat, he wanted to know how much his Rez is going to cost him to pay me. Being a patient man, I said ok. We are talking of a rez that might not even come. Yet, he wasted my time which I didn't mind and waited for the plat till he got the rez.<br />
<br />
He clearly had no intention of paying me. He surely had the money to pay me as the cleric declined his donation. He just logged off right after the rez in 30 seconds. The cleric gave him a hp buff after the rez and he was soon gone in 30 seconds. I had a hunch that he was logging off when he sat down which was why I started counting the 30 secs. <br />
<br />
__________________________________________________  ______________<br />
Now if you look at what you said and how different the story you posted here, well you can hopefully see how far apart your stories are. In your posting you damn near claim you had a contract for services but in your communication to me you &quot;figured he reimburse you&quot;.<br />
__________________________________________________  _______________ <br />
<br />
Its not at all &quot;far from different&quot; as you claim it to be. All I forgot to mention was that he promised to pay me after I summoned the corpse for him. Also, When I contacted you, I did tell you to visit the emarr forums for the full story and the proof of the screenshots. You didn't post a screenshot of our entire conversation which didnt last more than a minute. The full story on here is as detailed as it gets. which is why my tell has been to you has been hasty as the details were already posted here and it had been two days already since the incident occured.  What I think you are doing right now is.. you are twisting the words of my tell to make your guildie look good. Understandable, as thats whats probably I would have done if I were in your shoes. When I meant he didn't have the money for the coffin as in he didn't have the money for the coffin before summoning. I figured he'd pay me after I summoned it for him but he didnt. He told me the money is on his corpse and will be paid after I summoned it for him. He surely <b>HAD </b> the money on his corpse as his donation to the cleric was declined by her and his tell to me &quot;let me see how much a rez is going to cost him&quot;. I'm sure he had at least 175 pp on his corpse to say that. <br />
<br />
Why? If he was short of 175 pp he would have said, he didnt have the money to cover the cost of the coffin when he looted the corpse. I know that the cleric didnt take his donation when I asked her. All he had to do was just pay me after the cleric declined his donation. Or pay me atleast whatever amount he had on him. He did no such thing and logged  off. Yes, he had the money.<br />
<br />
Also, In my tell to you I didnt even request for the plat that was scammed. My tell to you was a warning of of a rotten apple in your guild and nothing more. <br />
<br />
Trust me, I'm not that rich to throw free coffins to every stranger that I meet. Which is why I only ask them to pay me the cost of the coffin. I will however never take any money from friends. If they payme, I'll take it. Usually My necro doesnt have any plat on him and my friends usually give me a coffin to summon their corpses. The summon corpse spell is a lvl 39 spell ( link -http://eq.crgaming.com/spells/spell.asp?Id=475 ) and he is a level 52 necro. He should have long bought the spell a long time ago or got it from Splitpaw as thats where it drops. His tell to my alt was that he didnt have the spell when I asked him if he tried summoning it. Then he didn't have the plat on him to cover the coffin expenses. <b>ALL</b> his plat was on the corpse. Something really doesn't add up here.<br />
__________________________________________________  _______________<br />
Also you didn&#8217;t make a log of your agreement unfortunately but then you did not feel you needed to but yet surprising to me you started counting to 30 as soon as the man sat down. Why did you find this strange , I always sit and med after a rez as most peeps do.  - Razuel<br />
__________________________________________________  _________________<br />
<br />
He logged off in 30 secs right after the rez. I'm sure he had a chance to &quot;med&quot; for 30 secs while logging. <br />
<br />
This was how it ended...<br />
At first he was facing me when I summoned the corpse for him. After the rez (he was still facing me) and the cleric gave him a buff. He then turned around with his back to me. Sat down.. (Thats when I started counting the 30 secs) and he was gone in 30 secs. Its insulting to someone when you do that.. especially after you helped him out.<br />
<br />
__________________________________________________  _________________<br />
With hope perhaps next time this sort of thing happens to you , you will also perhaps think of contacting the persons guild before feeling the need to post it here. Sorry for the lengthy reply and thank you to all who took the time to read it.  - Razuel<br />
__________________________________________________  _________________<br />
<br />
I did try contact you guys. But none of the officers were present when the incident happened. I waited for nearly two days before posting on here. I did however initially speak to someone named Tipp and told him what happened. And it was from him that I got your name. I didn't get to see you ingame until a few hours I had posted it on here. I had to warn the emarr community of this person ASAP before someone else runs into him and he gets a chance to scam them. <br />
<br />
What has happened to me, needs no further explanation or clarification from anyone (not even from Avalon Imperial Guards) which was why I posted it here. I didn't need to talk to anyone to &quot;solve&quot; the incident as there was no confusion as to what has happened. It was just a pure scam. I have written off the 175pp the minute he scammed me.<br />
<br />
__________________________________________________  ________________<br />
He said that he has looked for you since to pay you and has not found you to be on. -Razuel<br />
__________________________________________________  ________________<br />
<br />
I was on for an hour last night. Shidima too was on as he was added to my &quot;Friends&quot; list. I wish there was another list for me to add him to. He made no effort to contact me the hour I was on. He according to the list was in the zone OverThere. I didnt make any effort to contact him as I have already written off the plat.<br />
<br />
In conclusion, Sir, I do not need your 175 pp (as you didn't scam me and if you want to feel better please give the 175 pp to a newbie who is starting out). I donot want 175 pp from Shidima as well. The 175 pp was written off as a lesson well learnt.<br />
<br />
Morguen Graves,<br />
lvl 51 Necromancer.<br />
Emarr - (Not in a guild).</div>
