Evyla: As far as your comment what should I have done at that point? As I stated in first post I made I would have paid the debt, and second post even said I'd throw in a bit xtra.  But  after reading your last para I couldnt agree more and went back to the logs (as that was what I had concrete to go on).  So thank you for helping me to come to a different conclusion.  <br />
<br />
Davek: Many thanks to you.  Going by the management tool it does not look like someone earnest about repaying his debt quickly ( according to him) was making much of an effort.  You probably said the least but it carried more weight than most.  Now I could be wrong as maybe the guy had reasons he wasnt on sooner, rl issues  but as I do not see him as yet posting an apology here in my book it goes against him.<br />
<br />
Langree: thank you for seeing that I was /had apologised.  But in Morguens defense I have to say I didnt feel it was thrown back in my face.  He has been civil to me and I to him.  If we had done this via email to each other perhaps we <br />
would have came to the same conclussion.  As i said some peeps remarks have helped as well though.  Also I do believe he has told the truth and I too would feel irratated to have exasperated by someone telling even more untruths.<br />
<br />
<b>Morguen </b> :  You are the person this matters most too.  Once again my apology and as I said previously if you responded that it wasnt the truth that I would look into it again.  Well you have done such and so have I.  After taking some thoughts as I mentioned above it does raise more doubt as to my members story/defense.  I will be placing the matter in my officers hands for a vote on what will be done with the member.  The way I run my guild  we are all leaders and my vote is just one vote, however I will make my thoughts known to my officers.  As far as giving the payment to a nes player  no problem as I as many of us do that frequently.  As far as twisting words I do not see that but rather taking the logs both yours and mine for what they actually stated and tried to be cautious in coming to a conclussion.  To not do that would be unfair to any member and if a guild did not take interest in disecting an incident I wouldnt be in it,  As you know people dont always post the truth and sometimes go after another player out of some other reasons.  I hope you find this to be a positive out come and if I or my members can ever lend a hand please dont hesitate.  Thanks, Raz<br />
<br />
Grav and Kam : I know it must be tight up there but if you have the room put your glasses on and reread the posts, including the linked logs.  I didnt scam anyone so whats with the he got caught BS?  I merely got involved to try to resolve a wrong.  I also took time to try to find out both sides of the story but Im sure you two scholars would have just shook up your magic eight ball.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
